          <header class="reg-header">
            <h2>Registration Requirements</h2>
            <p class="subtitle">Guidelines for registration and licensing under the Royal Council of Veterinary Doctors (RCVD).</p>
          </header>

          <div class="card">
            <h3>Required Documents</h3>
            <ul class="styled-list">
              <li>Letter addressed to the Chairperson of RCVD</li>
              <li>Notified diploma/degree</li>
              <li>Copy of ID card</li>
              <li>Photo passport</li>
              <li>Bank slip of <strong>30,000 RWF</strong> deposited at RCVD account <strong>BK 0004000653033-35</strong></li>
              <li>Filled Application Form</li>
            </ul>
            <p><strong>Registration fees for foreigners:</strong> <span class="highlight">50,000 RWF</span></p>
            <p class="note"><strong>Attention:</strong> Fresh graduates registered within the first 6 months are waived for <strong>50%</strong> of registration fees.</p>
          </div>

          <h2 id="license">License</h2>
          <div class="card">
            <h3>Requirements</h3>
            <ul class="styled-list">
              <li>License application letter addressed to the Chairperson specifying 1–3 non-conflicting veterinary services and intended practice zone (district, sector).</li>
              <li>Copy of previous license (for practitioners already licensed).</li>
              <li>Business registration certificate or recommendation letter from the sector level.</li>
              <li>Color passport photo.</li>
              <li>Evidence of annual licensing fee payment (Bank of Kigali – RCVD 00040-00653033-35).</li>
              <li>Proof of participation in CPD activities — minimum 20 credit points per year (professionals) or 14 points (paraprofessionals).</li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <div class="card">
            <h3>Available Fields of Practice</h3>
            <div class="columns">
              <ul>
                <li>Curative and preventive veterinary medicine (veterinary clinic)</li>
                <li>Veterinary pharmacy practice and livestock equipment use</li>
                <li>Animal feeds and feeding</li>
                <li>Bovine artificial insemination</li>
                <li>Swine artificial insemination</li>
                <li>Hygiene and quality of animal products</li>
              </ul>
              <ul>
                <li>Wild animal medicine</li>
                <li>Animal resources extension &amp; advisory services</li>
                <li>Education</li>
                <li>Research</li>
                <li>Veterinary consultancy</li>
              </ul>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="card">
            <h3>Licensing Fees</h3>
            <table class="fees-table">
              <thead>
                <tr><th>Category</th><th>Fee (RWF)</th></tr>
              </thead>
              <tbody>
                <tr><td>Veterinary Doctors / Animal Scientists / Veterinary Technologists</td><td>30,000</td></tr>
                <tr><td>Veterinary Paraprofessionals A1</td><td>20,000</td></tr>
                <tr><td>Veterinary Paraprofessionals A2</td><td>15,000</td></tr>
                <tr><td>Provisional License</td><td>Free</td></tr>
                <tr><td>Foreigners (Professionals)</td><td>100,000</td></tr>
                <tr><td>Foreigners (Paraprofessionals)</td><td>50,000</td></tr>
              </tbody>
            </table>
          </div>

          <div class="card">
            <h3>Provisional License Requirements</h3>
            <ul class="styled-list">
              <li>Letter addressed to the Chairperson</li>
              <li>Copy of registration certificate</li>
              <li>Copy of ID</li>
              <li>Photo passport</li>
              <li>Declaration form completed by a Supervisor (5+ years experience)</li>
              <li>Copy of Supervisor’s license</li>
            </ul>
            <p class="note">Free of charge if requested during the internship period (first 6–12 months). Interns must secure placement before applying.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="card">
            <h3>Other Services</h3>
            <ul class="styled-list">
              <li>Registration of Companies under sanitary mandate</li>
              <li>Recommendation Letters for Veterinary Practitioners and Companies</li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <div class="card">
            <h3>Other Activities</h3>
            <ul class="styled-list">
              <li>Establish and enforce the veterinary code of ethics</li>
              <li>Promote self-respect, integrity, and professional secrecy</li>
              <li>Inspect veterinary practitioners, companies, and premises for compliance</li>
              <li>Conduct annual veterinary medicine and animal health school audits</li>
              <li>Enhance capacity building for professionals and paraprofessionals</li>
              <li>Manage disciplinary actions</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
